# Clean Code

## Functions

- Single responsibility -- one function does one thing
- Small: if a function needs a comment block explaining sections, split it
- Explicit return types on all exported functions
- Use dependency injection for external services (pass as parameter with a default)

## Naming

- Descriptive names that reveal intent -- no abbreviations
- Avoid generic names: `data`, `info`, `temp`, `result`, `item`, `stuff`
- Boolean variables/functions start with `is`, `has`, `can`, `should`
- Functions that return a value: noun or `get*`; functions that perform an action: verb

## Types

- No `any` -- use `unknown` + type narrowing when the type is truly unknown
- Prefer interfaces for object shapes, type aliases for unions/intersections
- Use `readonly` for data that should not be mutated

## Variables

- `const` by default; `let` only when reassignment is necessary; never `var`
- Declare variables close to where they are used
- No unused variables or imports (enforced by `deno lint`)

## Error handling

- Never swallow errors with empty catch blocks
- Throw descriptive `Error` messages that tell the user what went wrong and how to fix it
- Prefer custom error messages over re-throwing raw errors

## Dead code

- No commented-out code -- use version control instead
- Remove unused functions, imports, and variables before committing
